OK, Your picks for the week of 11/13/05:

Buffalo will be coming off a bye week and coach Mularkey is tweaking the O-line for the game against the KC Chiefs at the Ralph. Word has it he'll likely start Losman this week. KC at Buffalo? Close one with the Bills up 28-25

Gods own team - DA BEARZZZ - will be punishing the San Freekcisco 69...errr...49ers this sunday in Chicago.
 
 Thomas Jones re-bruised his ribs last sunday so look for the rookie, Cedric Benson from Texas, to bust loose for 200+ running yards. The kid ain't the brightest bulb but he's a horse and he's ready to bust out of the corral.
 
 Kyle Orton (QB) is developing nicely for a rookie. He is showing patience. He is making a minimum of rookie mistakes and is finally running out of the tackle-box/pocket and throwing the ball away when no one is open. He has a really crappy beard however...it actually makes him look even YOUNGER! 
 
 The spread is Bears by 12 1/2 as of today. It might be a good bet. Ex-Bear Mike Singeltary is a defensive coach for San Fran. 
 
 BEARZZZ 35 San Freekcisco 14
wow, bassman, good call. Buffalo dominated KC this week. And while Losman didn't start, he did end up stepping in for Holcomb. Good foresight.

Now, I'm don't usually pay attention to the Chiefs but since I do live in a KC suburb, that's most of the sports news I get. And I study Journalism and so I try to pay attention to the news. But if I understand it correctly, the player I'm mentioning was one of the star players. If he had been able to play, Bassman would have had a better chance at the accurate final score.
I'm so happy the Chiefs lost and kept themselves down in the AFC West against my BRONCOS!!! who won yet again my friends.

Dallas won one last night and it is always good to beat the Eagles, but I was very impressed by Donavan McNabb. The man is a warrior, playing hurt, but dangerous even when wounded.
 Dono
